data.organizationName: Ahmadiyya Muslim Students Association for Women
data.name: The Second Coming
data.description: This is an interfaith event around the topic of the second-coming of Jesus. We will be inviting people of different faiths to come talk about Jesus and his second coming. We will be inviting an Imam, Buddhist monk, Rabbi, Priest, and Hindu representative to this event to talk about the second coming of Jesus in their respective religions. Christians believe in the second coming of Jesus, Hindus believe in the second-coming of Jesus, Buddhist believe in the second coming of Maitreyu, and Ahmadiyyat has its own take of the second coming of Jesus. We will be discussing the similarities of our beliefs in this event in order to promote unity.

data.organizationName: Ahmadiyya Muslim Students Association for Women
data.name: The Astonishing Life of Muhammad
data.description: Our goal for this event is to talk about the life and story of the prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him). We will be having multiple speakers talk about his life from birth to death as well as the legacy he left as the prophet. We also will be presenting insights into the story of the Prophet, which the world otherwise may not have known as well as a unique perspective in response to recent caricatures and ridicule.This is a coed event. People of allfaiths and races are welcome to come to the event. If you have any questions or concerns please reach out to us.It will take place on Wednesday, March 8th at 7pm in the Busch Student Center Multipurpose Room B. Inshallah we hope to see you all there! Please RSVP ahead of time using this link.https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfUQXFAJAoHl2apUye6L2p8Av9BpjZjga7dJiIlJjYeijt7Cg/viewform
